stylometry: The regression equation (y=ax+b) shows the regression line, what is used to represent a scattered set of data with both independant and dependant variables. If we are looking at a model of apartment sales (sales = the dependant variable) according to price (price = the independant variable) we can set up the data with how many sales at particular prices. After filling this data into a chart, we can mathematically draw a line using the regression equation which will show the regression line. Different coefficients are used to analyze the exactness of this line including coefficient of determination, coefficient of correlation, standard error of the estimate, F, the siginificance of F, and many more.
